// § 4 — Divergence summary (no executable tests — documentation only)
//
// The following functions are present in bounty_escrow but have NO equivalent
// in this scaffold. Each gap is a potential security regression if real escrow
// logic is ever promoted to this crate without re-implementing them.
//
//   MISSING (HIGH priority):
//     - init / admin storage           → no admin role, no `require_auth`
//     - lock_funds                      → no escrow state, no token transfer
//     - release_funds                   → no fund release, no guard
//     - partial_release                 → no milestone tracking
//     - refund / approve_refund         → no refund path
//     - reentrancy guard (DataKey)      → not present
//     - Error enum (24 variants)        → not present
//
//   MISSING (MEDIUM priority):
//     - deadline enforcement            → no timestamp checks
//     - batch_lock_funds                → not present
//     - batch_release_funds             → not present
//     - claim / authorize_claim         → not present
//     - circuit breaker                 → not present
//     - pause flags                     → not present
//     - fee config                      → not present
//
//   ONLY IN SCAFFOLD (out of scope for this issue — just noted):
//     - `hello(env, to) -> Vec<String>` → not present in bounty_escrow
//
// Action: open a follow-up issue to either (a) promote the bounty_escrow
// implementation into this workspace or (b) formally retire this scaffold
// and remove it from CI.
